Subject: Re: [Ticket #{ticket_id}] — Incident Resolved

Hi {customer_name},

This is a follow-up to your report. The issue you experienced has been resolved.

Resolution time: {resolution_time} UTC
Full incident report: {status_page_url}/incidents/{incident_id}

{action_note}

If you continue to experience any issues after {resolution_time} UTC,
please reply to this ticket and we will investigate further.

Thank you for your patience.
{Support Team Name}

Subject: SLA Impact Report — {Service} Incident {incident_id}

Dear {customer_name},

This is your SLA impact report for the {service} incident that occurred on {date}.

Incident ID: {incident_id}
Severity: {severity}
Start time: {start_time} UTC
Resolution time: {resolution_time} UTC
Total duration: {duration_minutes} minutes

SLA credit calculation:
- Your contracted availability SLO: {contracted_slo}%
- Incident impact on your account: {impact_description}
- Credit applicable: {credit_amount_or_formula}

The credit will be applied to your next invoice. You do not need to
submit a claim.

A full incident report including root cause and preventive actions
will be published within {postmortem_days} business days.

For questions, contact your Technical Account Manager:
{tam_name} | {tam_email}
